<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06042e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06042e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06042e"> 42(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> heap earth / crush paper / empty drawer // power / brighter / self / sense</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Preyer, qui a observ&eacute; soigneusement les <i>exp&eacute;rimentations</i> sous forme de jeux auxquelles son fils s&apos;est successivement livr&eacute; du treizi&egrave;me au trente-troisi&egrave;me mois (par exemple: ouvrir et fermer une bo&icirc;te, <mark>vider, puis remplir un tiroir</mark>, accumuler du sable et le disperser, aligner des coquilles ou des pierres, vider et remplir des bouteilles</mark>, des arrosoirs, jeter des pierres dans l&apos;eau, etc.) &hellip;, attribue aussi la satisfaction que l&apos;enfant retirait de telles occupations &agrave; ce m&ecirc;me &ldquo;<mark>sentiment orgueilleux de jouer le r&ocirc;le de cause</mark>&rdquo;. <font color="green">[Preyer, who has carefully observed experiments in the form of games in which his son has successively delivered from the thirteenth to the thirty-third month (for example: open and close a box, empty, then fill a drawer, accumulate sand and disperse it, aligning shells or stones, emptying and filling bottles, watering cans, throwing stones into the water, etc.) [&hellip;]</font> also attributes the satisfaction that the child derived from such occupations to this same &ldquo;proud feeling of playing the role of cause&rdquo;]. <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 51</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
